WEBVTT

00:07:27.768 --> 00:07:30.934
feel that, actually,
logic is its own answer.

00:07:31.503 --> 00:07:34.409
What they don't say is,
"Well, the numbers all seem to add up,

00:07:34.433 --> 00:07:37.885
but before I present this idea,
I'll show it to some really crazy people

00:07:37.909 --> 00:07:40.275
to see if they can come up with
something better."

00:07:40.299 --> 00:07:43.054
And so we -- artificially,
I think -- prioritize

00:07:43.078 --> 00:07:46.829
what I'd call mechanistic ideas
over psychological ideas.

00:07:47.577 --> 00:07:49.609
An example of a great psychological idea:

00:07:49.633 --> 00:07:52.249
the single best improvement
in passenger satisfaction

00:07:52.273 --> 00:07:53.577
on the London Underground,

00:07:53.601 --> 00:07:55.171
per pound spent,

00:07:55.195 --> 00:07:57.530
came when they didn't add
any extra trains,

00:07:57.554 --> 00:07:59.459
nor change the frequency of the trains;

00:07:59.483 --> 00:08:02.612
they put dot matrix display boards
on the platforms --